Donald T. Davis (don@cam.ov.com) wrote:

: does anyone have a figure for how much longer it takes
: to load a key into a des chip, than it takes to complete
: a single block's encryption?

See Hans Eberle, "A High-speed DES Implementation for Network 
Applications" in Crypto 92.

He describes a 100 Mb/sec DES chip which can change key on
each block at full speed.  He also reports work on a 1 Gb/sec
rate.

--Bryan
